World marathon record holder Brigid Kosgei, World 500m champion Hellen Obiri and World 3000m steeplechase gold medallist Beatrice Chepkoech have been nominated for the IAAF Female Athlete of the Year award. Kosgei, Obiri and Chepkoech are part of 11 nominees released by world athletics governing body, IAAF, for the annual award which will be decided on November 23 in Monaco, France. More to follow...  